postText:
Hello fellow mDome users! As you may have noticed we've made some slight changes regarding the playlist/tracklist module. From now on, track pages can be used to add songs to existing playlists, or to create a playlist "on the fly". Hope you like the changes.
Fellow mDome team.

Exploding Head, in my opinion, is better than their self-titled debut. It's dark industrial sounding noise rock at it's best. It sorta has a new wave feel to it throughout the whole album. All In All, A Place To Bury Strangers has crafted a pretty strange, psychedelic mix of noise in Exploding Head.
 
 Favorite tracks: 2. In Your Heart, 5. Keep Slipping Away, 7. Smile When You Smile, 8. Everything Always Goes Wrong
 
 Least favorite tracks: 6. Ego Death
 
Rating: 5
